  "text": "On the constructive side, while the scripting language used by Bitcoin is (intentionally) limited in its functionality, Bitcoin transactions can nevertheless store small amounts of arbitrary data. This makes Bitcoin potentially useful for other applications that may require the properties of its ledger, such as certifying the ownership and timestamp of a document [CITATION_1] . One mechanism that allows Bitcoin to store such data is the script opcode OP_RETURN, 2 which can be used to embed up to 80 bytes of arbitrary data.",
